physical_extent: 2 pts. in 1 v. (pt. 1: 21 leaves; pt. 2: 42 p.)
Drop-head title, dated at head: January 16. 1735. - Concerning a suit brought by John Cuninghame of Enterkine against Lady Enterkine for repairs.
Dated at head: February 7. 1735. - Concerning Colquhoun's administration of the estate of a minor.
Arr. on two staves for voice and keyboard; with a version for the flute.
1 p.l., 3 col. plates, 129 col. maps (part. fold.)

Caption title; with a docket title that reads 'Memorial of the agent for the province of Massachussetts-Bay against a duty of 3d. per gallon on foreign molasses.'. - Dated in MS '9th February, 1764' and signed J. Mauduit.
